    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Oxide appearing as an olive-brown or blue-black anhydrous powder when stannous oxalate is heated out of contact with the air. Uses include manufacturing of other tin compounds, as a reducing agent, and as an ingredient in creating ruby glass.</Note_Text>
